locations.name: Pretzel Place
locations.description:
Arbor Food Court
(Credit Card Accepted)
Delicious hot, buttered pretzels were created by a single mother determined to leave a legacy and provide for her children even though all the odds were stacked against her. Armed with a passion and with the help of her best friend, she created her secret recipe in their home kitchen, and began selling pretzels at local fairs and events.

Since then, The Pretzel Place has found a permanent home at First Monday Trade Days in Canton, Texas.

Fresh, Soft Pretzels, Garlic, Cinnamon sugar, Parmesan, Jalapeno Cheddar, Pepperoni, Handmade, Vanilla Icing, Cheese, Mustard,

locations.name: Henry Lewis Statue
locations.description: Standing tall at the Arbor Entrance, the statue of Henry Lewis honors the man whose vision helped shape First Monday into what it is today. With an open hand holding a silver dollar - his signature gesture of gratitude he would give every person he did business with. Henry is remembered not just as a mayor or businessman, but as a friend to the community. He once said, "Something to do. Something to see. You'll like it," and thanks to his legacy, generations still do.

locations.name: Rock House
locations.description:
Rockhouse offers a variety of tasty sandwiches and plates, all priced at $12. Their sandwiches come on homemade or Jalapeno Cheese buns and include options like Chicken Fried Chicken, Honey Fried Chicken with or without pimento, Chicken Fried Steak, Grilled Chicken, Pulled Pork, and even Grilled Cheese for $10. Each sandwich comes with your choice of one side.

For plates, you get to choose two sides, and the options include Chicken Fried Chicken, Chicken Fried Steak, Chicken Strips, and Grilled Chicken.

They also have nachos for $15 where you pick your chips or fries with nacho cheese, your meat (like chicken fried chicken, grilled chicken, pulled pork, chicken fried steak, or ground beef), and your toppings such as lettuce, tomato, onions, jalapenos, and pinto beans.

Sides are $3 each, with choices like crack green beans, homemade pinto beans, fries, fried okra, potato salad, coleslaw, and fried green beans (which cost $2 extra).

Drinks come in 20oz for $3 or 32oz for $5, with free refills on tea only. They have sweet and unsweet tea, sweet peach tea, Coke products, Sprite, Dr. Pepper, and water for $2.

They also offer a specialty item called the walking taco where you pick your chips (Fritos or Doritos), meat (ground beef or grilled chicken), and toppings like nacho cheese, lettuce, tomato, onions, jalapenos, pinto beans, and sour cream.

If you want to check out more about Rockhouse, you can find them on the First Monday Finder Map by searching "Rockhouse."

Pickles; Pickled Vegetables, Pickled Garlic, Stuffed Olives, Relishes, Pickled Quail Eggs, Sauces, Salsas, Quesos, Preserves, Jalapeno Jellies, Freezed Dried Candy.

Retired? Hardly. These spicy Southern gals (all in their glorious late 60s) are jarring up mischief and mouthwatering goodness one pickle at a time!

From Farmhouse Dills to Sweet Fire Pickles, their small-batch creations are packed with bold flavor and just a hint of attitude. Craving Cajun Pickle Sticks? Need a jar of Granny's Hot Sweet to wake up your sandwich? They've got you covered.

They also pickle anything that'll sit still long enough okra, green beans, carrots, beets, and even quail eggs (mild, spicy, or jalapeno... bless your heart).

And don't leave without a spoonful of their old-fashioned preserves - like blackberry, fig, or their dangerously addictive peach butter.

Come for the pickles, stay for the sass. These sisters have been stirring up trouble and brine since before you were born!

locations.description:
Trade Center 4: Booth 39
Step into the past with our collection of hand-tooled leather goods and Viking-inspired accessories. From Celtic knotwork belts and Norse-style bracers to Viking pouches, runic-etched knife sheaths, and leather-bound journals, each piece is a handcrafted tribute to ancient craftsmanship and warrior culture. While you shop, take a seat and challenge your mind with a round of Hnefataflalso known as Viking chess. Our custom-crafted game boards are more than just beautifultheyre a journey into the past, a test of strategy, and a celebration of Viking heritage. Its role in Norse history cannot be overstated, and now you can play the same game the Vikings once used to sharpen their wits before battle. Whether you're into reenactments, Renaissance fairs, cosplay, or just honoring the bold legacy of your ancestorsyoull find something here that speaks to your warrior spirit.

CityFields: 492427, 492428, 502392, 502393
JST Ranch & Timber, LLC, located in Poetry, TX, proudly offers a rugged lineup of tractor, skid-steer, and mini skid-steer attachments built for hard work on the ranch, jobsite, or homestead. Whether you’re moving hay, clearing brush, grading land, or tackling dirt work, we supply heavy-duty attachments that are made to last — including: • Grapples • Pallet forks • Land planes • Brush cutter blades & hubs • Bucket teeth & cutting edges • Hydraulic couplers, hoses, and cylinder kits All attachments are Made in the USA and compatible with standard quick-attach systems, including those for John Deere, Bobcat, Kubota, Toro Dingo, and more. We also stock a wide range of repair parts and wear items to keep your equipment operating smoothly all year long. As a family-run business in rural Texas, we understand the demands of ag, land clearing, and ranch work — and we back every product with real-world experience and dependable customer support. Stop by our booth to see, touch, and feel the quality of our attachments in person. We welcome questions and are happy to help you find the right solution for your property or operation. Made in the USA attachments, tractor attachments, skid steer attachments, mini skid steer, grapples, pallet forks, land plane, brush cutter parts, quick attach, loader implements, hay spear, construction attachments, equipment dealer, JST Ranch & Timber, Poetry TX, Canton Texas vendor
